Parser Platform API

Download OpenAPI specification:Download

Parsly: dev@parsly.com URL: http://parsly.com

Parsly services for invoice documents and analysis data. Uploaded invoice documents are processed by a invoice parser engine, and the resulting analysis data is then made available for each document.

The dropzone service provide endpoints for uploading invoice files. Supported upload formats are:

  • application/pdf
  • image/jpg
  • image/png

A file can either describe one invoice, or part of a invoice document. Dropzone expects all files needed to describe a complete invoice when called, whereby it will create a document resource to keep track of all related source files. Exactly how the files are uploaded depend on which endpoint is used.

Invoice documents are processed asynchronouysly, and to determine when the analysis result is available, you should poll their status via the Pickup service. Document processing status are:

Status Description
Pending Resource created but file sources not yet uploaded.
Uploaded All file sources have been uploaded.
Compiled Available file sources compiled into a single document object.
Processed Invoice document processed by the parser engine.
Invalid Document is not a valid invoice.

When a file reaches the Processing status, the corresponding analysis data will be available via the Pickup service.

Upload a document via one or more files.

Upload a document via one or more files. Limited to 10 MB maximum total payload size.

Authorizations:
Parser_Platform_API_ApiKeyHeader
query Parameters
uploadId
string (Parser_Platform_API_ResourceId) [ 8 .. 256 ] characters ^[a-zA-Z0-9]+[a-zA-Z0-9\-]*[a-zA-Z0-9]+$
Example: uploadId=40DA103E-D405-4205-B716-1ACA27758687

User-definable ID. Must be unique for each resource type. Automatically generated if not provided by user.

Request Body schema: multipart/form-data
required

One or more invoice files via Multipart-Formdata content type.

file
Array of strings <binary> [ items <binary > ]

Form field containing an invoice encoded as binary data and limited to the following content types:

  • application/pdf
  • image/jpg
  • image/png

Accepts the internal HTTP header X-File-Id providing a user-definable ID. Automatically generated if not provided.

Pickup

Facilities to manage documents and retrieve invoice parser results.

List Uploaded Documents.

List uploaded documents. Note that the response is paginated, so the list may not contain all available documents. Use the pageSize query parameter to change the number of documents to include in the list, and use the pageId query parameter to step through the available pages. When the list is empty, the last page has been reached. The total number of available documents is available via the X-Total-Count response header.

Authorizations:
Parser_Platform_API_ApiKeyHeader
query Parameters
pageId
integer >= 1
Default: 1

ID of page to request (count starts from 1).

pageSize
integer [ 10 .. 50 ]
Default: 20

Number of items to include per page.

status
string (Parser_Platform_API_DocumentStatus)
Enum: "Pending" "Uploaded" "Compiled" "Processed" "Invalid"
Example: status=Compiled

Filter by document processing status.

valid
boolean

Filter by document with valid or invalid result when compared to a reference result.

reference
boolean

Filter by document with or without a reference result.

supplierId
string [ 14 .. 24 ] characters ^[0-9]+$
Example: supplierId=134987239478297

Filter documents by supplier id.

refSupplierId
string [ 2 .. 256 ] characters
Example: refSupplierId=sup-f43ebe84873d44968a402046ca68c112

Filter documents by reference supplier id.

externalIds[]
Array of strings (Parser_Platform_API_ResourceId) [^[a-zA-Z0-9]+[a-zA-Z0-9\-]*[a-zA-Z0-9]+$]
Example: externalIds[]=40DA103E-D405-4205-B716-1ACA27758687

Filter documents by external ids.

sort
string
Enum: "created_at:asc" "created_at:desc"

Sort documents by created-at timestamp in ascending or descending order.

createdBefore
string <date-time>

Filter documents by before created-at timestamp.

createdAfter
string <date-time>

Filter documents by after created-at timestamp.

search
string [ 2 .. 128 ] characters

Filter documents by string search on external id.

path Parameters

query Parameters

The start date against which to filter.

The end date against which to filter.

Default: ""

Search string which, if given, is used to filter against the list of applicable articles. Only articles with title or supplier article ID matching the search string are considered. Note that the match is case insensitive. By default, all applicable articles are considered.

leastSum
number
Default: 0

The minimum total sum against which to filter the list of applicable articles. Only articles whose total sum is equal to, or greater than, the given minimum are considered. By default, the minimum is zero.

string
Default: "all"
Enum: "all" "onlyNegotiated" "onlyNonNegotiated"

Whether to filter articles against currently active deals. Given onlyNegotiated, then only consider articles that have one or more currently active deals. Given onlyNonNegotiated, then only consider articles that do not have currently active deals. Given all, which is the default option, consider all applicable articles.
